00:17:36,235 --> 00:17:38,156
is not really on playtesting, but we do use these a lot

440
00:17:38,216 --> 00:17:40,337
in playtesting in terms of determining

441
00:17:40,357 --> 00:17:42,137
how people are consuming our levels.

442
00:17:42,497 --> 00:17:44,438
You can actually do, and I had to cut these slides,

443
00:17:44,478 --> 00:17:47,499
unfortunately, you can actually do quantification

444
00:17:47,759 --> 00:17:49,600
of eye movements and determine kind of what

